\f0\b 1. Installing and Configuring Software, Hardware, and Networks:\

\f1\b0 \

\f0\b Software Installation:
\f1\b0  Understand the different types of software (e.g., operating systems, applications, drivers) and the methods to install them (e.g., via installation wizards, command line, package managers).\
\

\f0\b Hardware Configuration: 
\f1\b0 Involves setting up physical components like 
\f0\b CPUs, GPUs, RAM, storage, and peripheral devices.
\f1\b0  Learn about 
\f0\b BIOS/UEFI settings, hardware drivers, and compatibility
\f1\b0  checks.\
\

\f0\b Network Configuration:
\f1\b0  Includes setting up 
\f0\b routers
\f1\b0 , 
\f0\b switches
\f1\b0 , and 
\f0\b firewalls
\f1\b0 , configuring
\f0\b  IP addresses
\f1\b0 , 
\f0\b subnets
\f1\b0 , 
\f0\b DNS
\f1\b0 , and 
\f0\b gateways
\f1\b0 . Understanding the basics of 
\f0\b TCP/IP
\f1\b0  and network topologies is essential.\
\

\f0\b 2. Monitoring System Performance and Troubleshooting Issues:\

\f1\b0 \

\f0\b System Monitoring: 
\f1\b0 Use tools like Task Manager 
\f0\b (Windows)
\f1\b0 , Activity Monitor 
\f0\b (macOS)
\f1\b0 , or top
\f0\b  (Linux)
\f1\b0  to monitor 
\f0\b CPU,
\f1\b0  
\f0\b memory
\f1\b0 , 
\f0\b disk usage
\f1\b0 , and 
\f0\b network
\f1\b0  activity. Learn about more advanced tools like 
\f0\b Nagios, Zabbix,
\f1\b0  or 
\f0\b SolarWinds
\f1\b0  for enterprise-level monitoring.\
\

\f0\b Troubleshooting:
\f1\b0  Identify and resolve issues related to hardware failures, software errors, and network problems. Learn systematic approaches like the 
\f0\b OSI 
\f1\b0 model for network troubleshooting and using logs 
\f0\b (event logs, syslog)
\f1\b0  for diagnostics.\
\

\f0\b 3. Ensuring Security and Efficiency of IT Infrastructure:\

\f1\b0 \

\f0\b Security:
\f1\b0  Implement 
\f0\b firewalls, antivirus software, and encryption. 
\f1\b0 Regularly update systems to patch vulnerabilities. Understand concepts like 
\f0\b VPNs
\f1\b0 , secure authentication methods 
\f0\b (MFA)
\f1\b0 , and access control.\
\

\f0\b Efficiency:
\f1\b0  Optimise resource usage by balancing 
\f0\b workloads, automating repetitive tasks, and ensuring systems 
\f1\b0 are 
\f0\b running
\f1\b0  the 
\f0\b latest, most efficient versions of software.
\f1\b0 \
\

\f0\b 4. Creating and Maintaining Documentation:
\f1\b0 \
\

\f0\b Documentation:
\f1\b0  Keep detailed records of 
\f0\b system configurations, network setups, troubleshooting procedures,
\f1\b0  and any changes made to the 
\f0\b IT 
\f1\b0 environment. Tools like 
\f0\b Confluence, SharePoint, or even simple wiki platforms
\f1\b0  can be used to organise and maintain this documentation.\
